n, yet the route still does not credibly achieve glutamine under known prebiotic conditions.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_002\",\n        \"rxn_015\",\n        \"rxn_016\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Tie FeS amination to specific reported temperatures and sulfur conditions.\",\n        \"Model glutamine as a fleeting side product if retained at all.\",\n        \"Distinguish literature-supported glutamate chemistry from literature-gap glutamine chemistry more sharply.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.88,\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.55,\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_007\": 0.84,\n        \"rxn_014\": 0.7,\n        \"rxn_015\": 0.5,\n        \"rxn_016\": 0.18\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.63,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.85,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.89,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.22,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.64,\n      \"feedback\": \"This route is one of the best aligned with recent glutamate literature because it combines a plausible alpha-ketoglutarate route with documented pyrite photocatalytic amination. It still fails at the glutamine step, which remains speculative and likely outcompeted by cyclization/deamidation.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_002\",\n        \"rxn_015\",\n        \"rxn_016\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Emphasize pyrite photochemistry as support for glutamate synthesis only.\",\n        \"Incorporate degradation competition directly into pathway sequence after rxn_016.\",\n        \"Avoid presenting target formation as achieved rather than conjectured.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.86,\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_008\": 0.92,\n        \"rxn_014\": 0.7,\n        \"rxn_015\": 0.5,